            {
                "label": "b",
                "content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "(a) On Fig. 3.1, complete the circuit to show a voltmeter connected to measure the potential difference (p.d.) across the terminals P and Q. [1]",
                        "bbox": [
                            115,
                            468,
                            917,
                            501
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "(b) The student measures the potential difference \\(V\\) across the parallel combination of resistors \\(R_1\\) and \\(R_2\\) and measures the current \\(I\\) in the circuit.",
                        "bbox": [
                            115,
                            515,
                            916,
                            548
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "His readings are shown in Fig. 3.2 and Fig. 3.3.",
                        "bbox": [
                            155,
                            561,
                            546,
                            578
                        ]
